The Zondo Commission will continue to hear South African Airways related evidence from the Head of Department: Procurement at South African Airways Technical: Nontsasa Memela. JOHANNESBURG - The state capture inquiry will continue to hear South African Airways-related testimony on Friday. The commission will hear SAA related testimony from former head of the procurement department at South African Airways Technical, Nontsasa Memela. On Thursday, acting head of Supply Chain Management at the South African Airways Technical, Schalk Hendrik Human testified before the commission. Human told the Zondo commission that SAA has to pay R500-million it never budgeted to ARR, a US company that received a tender to provide aircraft components.